INTRODUCTION
shucg.vim is a vim plugin for the class of 2011 students of Shanghai University to interact with 
the CourseGrading system in vim. But it should work with any other CourseGrading sites.

The official site of the CourseGrading system: course.sei.buaa.edu.cn

The pcg.py can be used as a normal python module to interact with the CourseGrading system.
pcg.py depends on the BeautifulSoup4 module and the poster module.
The assemble.sh is merely a simple bash script to combine LICENSE declaration, pcg.py and vcg.vim
and produce the shucg.vim file.

shucg.vim require vim compiled with +python option to run.
*************************************************************************************************
USAGE

On Ubuntu12.04

sudo apt-get install python-setuptools
sudo easy_install pip
sudo pip install bs4
sudo pip install poster

copy the shucg.vim file to ~/.vim/plugin
open shucg.vim with a text editor
find the "======CONFIGURE YOUR ACCOUNT HERE!!======" line
change USERNAME, PASSWORD, SITEURL, SCOPE for yours
**THE PLUGIN WILL TAKE EFFECT ONLY WHEN THE WORK DIRECTORY IS THE SAME AS SCOPE**

